N2  - Theorists in various fields have discussed characteristics of top managers. This paper attempts to synthesize these previously fragmented literatures around a more general ?upper echelons perspective.? The theory states that organizational outcomes?strategic choices and performance levels?are partially predicted by managerial background characteristics. Propositions and methodological suggestions are included.
