N2  - Analyzed are 32 established organizational science theories in terms of their rated importance, validity, and usefulness. Little evidence of any relationships among these three variables is found. However, other significant findings do emerge from the analyses. Their relevance for an emerging organizational science discipline is explored. Certain parameters of such a discipline are specified.
